# Testing Conventions — host-site

- Vitest + React Testing Library. No Jest — don't add it, don't add
  Jest-only APIs or config.
- Query the DOM by role/label/text (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`), never by
  a `data-testid` you had to add just for the test, unless there's genuinely
  no accessible way to select the element.
- Mock network calls with `msw` request handlers, not by stubbing `fetch`
  directly — tests should exercise real request/response parsing.
- One behavior per `it(...)` block. If a test needs "and also" in its
  description, split it.
- Hooks are tested with `renderHook` from `@testing-library/react`, wrapped
  in a `QueryClientProvider` test helper — see `src/test/` for the shared
  wrapper.
